TY  - JOUR
T1  - Currency Depreciation, Hoarding, and Relative Prices
AU  - Dornbusch, Rudiger
Y1  - 1973/07/01
PY  - 1973
DA  - 1973/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/260087
DO  - 10.1086/260087
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 893
EP  - 915
VL  - 81
IS  - 4
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - This paper investigates the effects of devaluation in a two-commodity, two- country, and two-money model with full employment and price flexibility. Primary emphasis is placed on the effect of a change in the real value of money on real expenditure and on the effects on relative prices of a redistribution of expenditure between countries. The stability properties of the model are related to the transfer problem in barter theory and to the Marshall-Lerner condition. Given stability, it is shown that a devaluation will improve the balance of payments.
AB  - This paper investigates the effects of devaluation in a two-commodity, two- country, and two-money model with full employment and price flexibility. Primary emphasis is placed on the effect of a change in the real value of money on real expenditure and on the effects on relative prices of a redistribution of expenditure between countries. The stability properties of the model are related to the transfer problem in barter theory and to the Marshall-Lerner condition. Given stability, it is shown that a devaluation will improve the balance of payments.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/260087
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/260087
Y2  - 2024/03/22
